	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=251710"><span id=" ">Rathenecro</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">105 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.27]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have one and a Scythe of Sundering in main hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;The effect is now Burning Affliction 4, so you won't have to bug the mages for a Rallican's anymore.  Oddly enough I have seen a necro carrying TWO of these.  They are No Drop, but they are not Lore.  The effect doesn't stack and cause double the affliction bonus, but the HP are nice enough.<br/><br/>To anyone who said it's a crappy weapon, well ESAD.  Until you get your Miragul's Robe with the 30% damage focus from Vengeance of Eternity, this is probably one of the best necro items around pre-Time.  It has HP, STA, mana, +12 to all resists, int if you still need and BA4.  When I got this I was able to free up a type 2 augmentation slot and get another resist aug instead of my Bloodied Stone of Vengeance aug.  You can use in primary or offhand, AND you can cart 2 around!<br/><br/>It might be EASIER to get Saryrn's Miserable bauble earring than it is to get this, since you go through an annoying timesink to get this, but I am not sorry I camped those damn shards for my VT key.  A VERY nice weapon indeed.</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />70 Deathspeaker<br/>Grand Occultist Vermilya<br/><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189873" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189873</a> </td></tr>
